ts.Beautifully illustrated with colour plates and black and white illustrations, this book will be valuable to those interested in stained glass and the wider world of Victorian art.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGlass painting and stainingzGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aGothic revival (Art)zGreat Britain. 4aGothic 2017. 7aART / History / General.2bisacsh  aGothic Revival.  aVictorian aesthetics.  aVictorian culture.  aart history.  acultural exchange.  acultural history.  aecclesiology.  aglass-painting.  anineteenth-century.  astained glass windows.1 aCheshire, Jim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612565140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526125651423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526125651/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles